.TH "_assert_hardreset" 9 "_assert_hardreset" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
_assert_hardreset \- assert the HW reset line of submodules contained in the hwmod module.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" _assert_hardreset
.BI "(struct omap_hwmod *oh "  ","
.BI "const char *name "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "oh" 12
struct omap_hwmod *
.IP "name" 12
name of the reset line to lookup and assert
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Some IP like dsp, ipu or iva contain processor that require an HW
reset line to be assert / deassert in order to enable fully the IP.
Returns -EINVAL if \fIoh\fP is null, -ENOSYS if we have no way of
asserting the hardreset line on the currently-booted SoC, or passes
along the return value from \fB_lookup_hardreset\fP or the SoC's
assert_hardreset code.
